    • createFamilyVariationBox

      private JComponent createFamilyVariationBox()
      Panel with fields and check boxes for selecting rate variation across families. Initializes gamma_duplicationT, gamma_gainT, gamma_lengthT and gamma_lossT, forbidden_duplicationCB, forbidden_gainCB. Initally, all check boxes are unselected, and all text field values are unset. Loss variation is disabled for now (not editable, not enabled, not visible).
      Returns:
      a container

    • createAlgorithmBox

      private JComponent createAlgorithmBox​(boolean want_optimization, boolean want_simulation)
      Panel with fields for convergence criteria. Initializes epsT and roundT. Initially, field values are unset.
      Returns:
      a container

    • createFamilyVariationParameterBox

      private JComponent createFamilyVariationParameterBox()
      Panel for rate variation (across families) parameters. Initialzes alpha_lengthT, alpha_gainT, alpha_duplicationT, alpha_lossT, forbidden_gainT, forbidden_duplicationT. Initially field values are unset, and check boxes are unselected.
      Returns:
      a container

    • createRootPriorParameterBox

      private JComponent createRootPriorParameterBox()
      Panel for root prior parameters Initializes root_aT, root_bT, fixed_rootCB, root_distributionL, root_aL and root_bL. Label texts are expected to be set when root prior is set.
      Returns:
      a container

    • setSelectedModel

      private void setSelectedModel​(int idx)
      Called when the selected initial model changes in the GUI (modelRB radio buttons). Performs model type and root prior selection by programmatic clicks, and sets other GUI component states accordingly to the newly selected model.
      Parameters:
      idx - the newly selected model

    • synchronizeOptimizationOptions

      private void synchronizeOptimizationOptions()

    • synchronizeModelStructureStates

      private void synchronizeModelStructureStates()
      Sets the states for fields and checkboxes related to gain and duplication rate in model. Field values may be reset if a rate feature is removed from the model. Used by listeners in initListeners().

    • synchronizeRootPriorMean

      private void synchronizeRootPriorMean()
      Updates the displayed value of the distribution mean (root_meanT) based on the values in the GUI.

    • synchronizeRootPriorStates

      private void synchronizeRootPriorStates()
      Sets the state for displayed fields and labels for a given root prior distribution. Field values are not set if they are null. Field values are set (to 0.1) only if the new distribution class has invalid parameter in the field. Used by listeners, called when selection of selected model changes in the GUI.
